title: Indian Masala dosa in the summer
description: A crispy, rice-batter crepe encases a spicy mix of mashed potato, which is then dipped in coconut chutney, pickles, tomato-and-lentil-based sauces and other condiments.

title: Spanish Seafood paella in the summer
description: Shrimp, lobster, mussels and cuttlefish combine with white rice and various herbs, oil and salt in this Valencian dish to send you immediately into holiday mode.

title: Mexican Tacos in the summer
description: A fresh, handmade tortilla stuffed with small chunks of grilled beef rubbed in oil and sea salt then covered with guacamole, salsa, onions, cilantro or anything else you want -- perfect for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

title: British Fish 'n' chips in the summer
description: The staple of the Victorian British working class is a crunchy-outside, soft-inside dish of simple, un-adorned fundamentals.

title: Italian Lasagna in the summer
description: Second only to pizza in the list of famed Italian foods, there's a reason this pasta-layered, tomato-sauce-infused, minced-meaty gift to kids and adults alike is so popular -- it just works.

title: Mozambican Piri-piri chicken in the summer
description: A finger-lickin' feast of chicken cooked with lime, pepper, garlic, coconut milk and piri piri sauce.

title: Thai Tom yum goong in the summer
description: This best food Thai masterpiece teems with shrimp, mushrooms, tomatoes, lemongrass, galangal and kaffir lime leaves. Usually loaded with coconut milk and cream.

title: German Hamburger in the summer
description: The bread-meat-salad combination is so good that entire countries have ravaged their eco-systems just to produce more cows.

title: Neapolitan pizza in the summer
description: With just a few ingredients -- dough, tomatoes, olive oil, salt and basil -- the Neapolitans created a food that few make properly, but everyone enjoys thoroughly.

title: Danish Red berry pudding with cream (Rødgrød med flød) in the summer
description: The hallmark dessert and all time classic dessert of Denmark.
